PREP: CLEAN: Wash hands. Pierce potatoes with fork. Microwave at HIGH 11 to 15 minutes or until tender, rearranging once. Meanwhile, cut chicken into thin strips. CLEAN: Wash hands. In small bowl, blend broth, soy sauce, pepper and cornstarch; set aside. COOK: Spray a large nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Heat over medium-high heat. Add chicken and garlic. Cook and stir 3 minutes. Add pepper and squash; cook 1 minute. Add asparagus and pea pods; cook and stir 2 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender and internal juices of chicken run clear. (Or insert instant-read meat thermometer in thickest part of chicken. Temperature should read 180 degrees F.) Blend in broth mixture. Cook and stir until broth is thickened and translucent. SERVE: Serve chicken and vegetable mixture over potatoes. Serve with cornbread, if desired. CHILL: Refrigerate leftovers immediately.